SUPLINF.P:
During its 7-year lookback review, DOE is directed by EPCA to evaluate whether an amended test procedure would more accurately or fully comply with the representativeness and burden requirements in 42 U.S.C. 6314(a)(2), and if DOE determines an amended test procedure would do so, then DOE is required to prescribe such test procedures for the equipment class. (42 U.S.C. 6314(a)(1)(A)) There is no requirement that DOE's decision to amend a test procedure be supported by clear and convincing evidence. (
Id.
) DOE's 7-year-lookback review under EPCA ensures that DOE is not bound to an industry test procedure that has not been updated when more representative and/or less burdensome test methods are available.
